ut_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":532},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"34b0f619-6199-46c8-890a-2dbb6ab633bf\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:97:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_019QJpNuD5srNEpDDznjEPZP\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"(Bash completed with no output)\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"5828ebdf-2656-4eb1-91ff-3d5a5106f485\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-03T18:32:59.802Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":true}}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:98:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_0175eNHhuPCVKP2fCzwGKLeC\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01PnyXzB9vHCmPhoUC9V5Xah\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/output/cloud_deployment_plan.md\",\"content\":\"# Cloud Deployment Plan — Kalshi Trading Pipeline\\n**Author**: Quinn (Cloud Engineer)\\n**Task**: T267\\n**Date**: 2026-04-03\\n**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP notes where applicable\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nDeploy the Kalshi trading pipeline as a containerized workload on AWS. The system consists of three processes:\\n\\n| Process | Source | Port | Description |\\n|---------|--------|------|-------------|\\n| `kalshi-dashboard` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js` | 3200 | Trade signals API |\\n| `kalshi-scheduler` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/run_scheduler.sh` | — | Runs `live_runner.js` every 10 min |\\n| `kalshi-monitor` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/monitor.js` | — | Alerts if pipeline stalls |\\n\\nA one-person operator can deploy this in a single day following the steps below.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n```\\nInternet\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nRoute 53 (optional domain)\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nALB (HTTPS :443 → HTTP :3200)\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nECS Fargate Task (trading-pipeline)\\n  ├── kalshi-dashboard    :3200\\n  ├── kalshi-scheduler    (no port — cron loop)\\n  └── kalshi-monitor      (no port — polling loop)\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nAWS Secrets Manager\\n  └── KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY\\n```\\n\\nNo database required. Trade signals are written to JSON files; PnL state is file-based. EFS mounts the `agents/bob/output/` directory for persistence across task restarts.\\n\\n**Monthly cost estimate** (us-east-1, on-demand):\\n| Resource | Config | $/month |\\n|----------|--------|---------|\\n| ECS Fargate | 0.25 vCPU / 512 MB, 24×7 | ~$9 |\\n| ALB | 1 instance | ~$18 |\\n| EFS | < 1 GB | < $1 |\\n| Secrets Manager | 2 secrets | $0.80 |\\n| CloudWatch Logs | ~1 GB/mo | ~$0.50 |\\n| **Total** | | **~$29/month** |\\n\\nTo cut cost to ~$11/month: drop the ALB and expose the dashboard directly (no HTTPS) — acceptable for a single-operator internal tool.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Container Choice: AWS Fargate\\n\\n**Why Fargate over EC2:**\\n- No instance management, patching, or AMI rotation\\n- Scales to zero when stopped; billing is per-second\\n- Sufficient for a single trading pipeline (scheduler runs every 10 min, CPU burst only)\\n\\n**Why not Lambda:**\\n- The scheduler is a `while true; sleep 600` loop — Lambda's max execution time (15 min) doesn't fit\\n- live_runner.js needs persistent file output between runs\\n\\n**Why not GCP Cloud Run:**\\n- Existing Terraform modules are AWS-native (ECS, ALB, EFS, Secrets Manager)\\n- Switch to GCP Cloud Run only if Kalshi API latency to GCP us-central1 is significantly better\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Environment Variables\\n\\nInjected at runtime from **AWS Secrets Manager** — never hardcoded in container or task definition.\\n\\n| Variable | Required | Description |\\n|----------|----------|-------------|\\n| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Yes (live trading) | Kalshi REST API key — obtain from kalshi.com |\\n| `KALSHI_DEMO` | No | `\\\"false\\\"` = live mode; default = demo/paper mode |\\n| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Yes (production) | Bearer token for `/api/*` auth on port 3200 |\\n| `PAPER_TRADING` | No | Default `true` — set `\\\"false\\\"` only after founder approval |\\n| `NODE_ENV` | Yes | `\\\"production\\\"` |\\n| `PORT` | Yes | `3200` (dashboard API) |\\n\\n**Critical**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` is the default and must remain so until founder explicitly approves live order submission (per team consensus rule #1).\\n\\n### Secrets Manager setup (one-time)\\n```bash\\n# Create secrets\\naws secretsmanager create-secret \\\\\\n  --name \\\"tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\\\" \\\\\\n  --secret-string \\\"YOUR_KALSHI_API_KEY\\\"\\n\\naws secretsmanager create-secret \\\\\\n  --name \\\"tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\\\" \\\\\\n  --secret-string \\\"$(openssl rand -hex 32)\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Deployment Steps (Day 1)\\n\\n### Prerequisites\\n- AWS account with CLI configured (`aws configure`)\\n- Docker installed locally\\n- Terraform >= 1.6\\n- Node.js 20 (for local build/test)\\n\\n### Step 1: Build and push container image (~15 min)\\n\\n```bash\\n# From aicompany/ root\\ncd /path/to/aicompany\\n\\n# Create ECR repo (one-time)\\naws ecr create-repository --repository-name tokenfly-trading --region us-east-1\\n\\n# Authenticate Docker to ECR\\naws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 \\\\\\n  | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin \\\\\\n    <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com\\n\\n# Build trading pipeline image\\ndocker build -f Dockerfile.trading -t tokenfly-trading:latest .\\n\\n# Tag and push\\ndocker tag tokenfly-trading:latest \\\\\\n  <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest\\ndocker push <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest\\n```\\n\\n### Step 2: Create Dockerfile.trading\\n\\nThe existing `Dockerfile` serves the agent dashboard. The trading pipeline needs its own image:\\n\\n```dockerfile\\n# Dockerfile.trading\\nFROM node:20-alpine\\n\\nRUN apk add --no-cache bash\\n\\nWORKDIR /app\\n\\n# Install production deps\\nCOPY agents/bob/backend/package.json agents/bob/backend/package-lock.json ./\\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\\n\\n# Copy trading pipeline source\\nCOPY agents/bob/backend/ ./\\n\\n# Create output directory for trade signals\\nRUN mkdir -p /app/output\\n\\nEXPOSE 3200\\n\\nENV NODE_ENV=production \\\\\\n    PORT=3200 \\\\\\n    PAPER_TRADING=true\\n\\n# Start all three processes via PM2\\nRUN npm install -g pm2\\nCMD [\\\"pm2-runtime\\\", \\\"ecosystem.trading.config.js\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n### Step 3: Create PM2 config for trading processes\\n\\n```javascript\\n// ecosystem.trading.config.js\\nmodule.exports = {\\n  apps: [\\n    {\\n      name: \\\"kalshi-dashboard\\\",\\n      script: \\\"dashboard_api.js\\\",\\n      instances: 1,\\n      env: { NODE_ENV: \\\"production\\\", PORT: \\\"3200\\\" },\\n    },\\n    {\\n      name: \\\"kalshi-scheduler\\\",\\n      script: \\\"dashboard/run_scheduler.sh\\\",\\n      interpreter: \\\"bash\\\",\\n      instances: 1,\\n    },\\n    {\\n      name: \\\"kalshi-monitor\\\",\\n      script: \\\"dashboard/monitor.js\\\",\\n      instances: 1,\\n    },\\n  ],\\n};\\n```\\n\\n### Step 4: Provision infrastructure with Terraform (~10 min)\\n\\nUse the existing `infrastructure/` modules. Create a new `trading` environment or reuse `dev`:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd infrastructure/environments/dev   # or create environments/trading/\\n\\n# terraform.tfvars (trading-specific)\\ncat > terraform.tfvars <<EOF\\nenv                  = \\\"trading\\\"\\naws_region           = \\\"us-east-1\\\"\\nvpc_cidr             = \\\"10.1.0.0/16\\\"\\navailability_zones   = [\\\"us-east-1a\\\", \\\"us-east-1b\\\"]\\npublic_subnet_cidrs  = [\\\"10.1.0.0/24\\\", \\\"10.1.1.0/24\\\"]\\nprivate_subnet_cidrs = [\\\"10.1.2.0/24\\\", \\\"10.1.3.0/24\\\"]\\nnat_gateway_count    = 1\\ntask_cpu             = 256\\ntask_memory          = 512\\ndesired_count        = 1\\nmin_capacity         = 1\\nmax_capacity         = 1\\nimage_tag            = \\\"latest\\\"\\nEOF\\n\\nterraform init\\nterraform plan    # review — should create ~35 resources\\nterraform apply\\n```\\n\\n### Step 5: Deploy ECS task definition\\n\\nThe `infrastructure/modules/ecs` module creates the ECS service. Override the container definition to point to the trading image and inject secrets:\\n\\nAdd to `infrastructure/modules/ecs/main.tf` (or create `infrastructure/modules/trading_task/`):\\n\\n```hcl\\n# ECS Task Definition — Trading Pipeline\\nresource \\\"aws_ecs_task_definition\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  family                   = \\\"${var.name_prefix}-trading\\\"\\n  requires_compatibilities = [\\\"FARGATE\\\"]\\n  network_mode             = \\\"awsvpc\\\"\\n  cpu                      = 256\\n  memory                   = 512\\n  execution_role_arn       = aws_iam_role.ecs_execution.arn\\n  task_role_arn            = aws_iam_role.ecs_task.arn\\n\\n  container_definitions = jsonencode([\\n    {\\n      name  = \\\"trading-pipeline\\\"\\n      image = \\\"${var.ecr_repo_url}:${var.image_tag}\\\"\\n      portMappings = [{ containerPort = 3200, hostPort = 3200 }]\\n      \\n      secrets = [\\n        {\\n          name      = \\\"KALSHI_API_KEY\\\"\\n          valueFrom = \\\"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\\\"\\n        },\\n        {\\n          name      = \\\"DASHBOARD_API_KEY\\\"\\n          valueFrom = \\\"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\\\"\\n        }\\n      ]\\n\\n      environment = [\\n        { name = \\\"NODE_ENV\\\",       value = \\\"production\\\" },\\n        { name = \\\"PORT\\\",           value = \\\"3200\\\" },\\n        { name = \\\"PAPER_TRADING\\\",  value = \\\"true\\\" },   # NEVER false without founder approval\\n        { name = \\\"KALSHI_DEMO\\\",    value = \\\"true\\\" }\\n      ]\\n\\n      mountPoints = [\\n        {\\n          sourceVolume  = \\\"trading-output\\\"\\n          containerPath = \\\"/app/output\\\"\\n          readOnly      = false\\n        }\\n      ]\\n\\n      logConfiguration = {\\n        logDriver = \\\"awslogs\\\"\\n        options = {\\n          awslogs-group         = \\\"/ecs/${var.name_prefix}-trading\\\"\\n          awslogs-region        = var.aws_region\\n          awslogs-stream-prefix = \\\"ecs\\\"\\n        }\\n      }\\n\\n      healthCheck = {\\n        command     = [\\\"CMD-SHELL\\\", \\\"node -e \\\\\\\"require('http').get('http://localhost:3200/api/health', r => process.exit(r.statusCode===200?0:1)).on('error',()=>process.exit(1))\\\\\\\"\\\"]\\n        interval    = 30\\n        timeout     = 5\\n        retries     = 3\\n        startPeriod = 15\\n      }\\n    }\\n  ])\\n\\n  volume {\\n    name = \\\"trading-output\\\"\\n    efs_volume_configuration {\\n      file_system_id     = var.efs_file_system_id\\n      transit_encryption = \\\"ENABLED\\\"\\n      authorization_config {\\n        access_point_id = var.efs_access_point_id\\n        iam             = \\\"ENABLED\\\"\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Step 6: Verify deployment (~5 min)\\n\\n```bash\\n# Check ECS service status\\naws ecs describe-services \\\\\\n  --cluster tokenfly-trading \\\\\\n  --services trading-pipeline \\\\\\n  --query 'services[0].{status:status,running:runningCount,desired:desiredCount}'\\n\\n# Tail CloudWatch logs\\naws logs tail /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading --follow\\n\\n# Test dashboard API via ALB\\ncurl -H \\\"x-api-key: $DASHBOARD_API_KEY\\\" \\\\\\n  https://<ALB_DNS>/api/health\\n\\n# Confirm scheduler is running (look for 10-min cycle logs)\\naws logs filter-log-events \\\\\\n  --log-group-name /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading \\\\\\n  --filter-pattern \\\"Pipeline OK\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Scheduler: run_scheduler.sh on AWS\\n\\nThe scheduler (`dashboard/run_scheduler.sh`) runs as a sidecar process inside the same ECS task via PM2. It loops every 600 seconds calling `live_runner.js`.\\n\\n**Alternative: EventBridge Scheduler** (cleaner, more observable)\\n\\nIf the while-loop approach causes issues (e.g., task restarts lose state), migrate to EventBridge:\\n\\n```bash\\n# Create EventBridge rule — runs every 10 minutes\\naws scheduler create-schedule \\\\\\n  --name kalshi-pipeline-run \\\\\\n  --schedule-expression \\\"rate(10 minutes)\\\" \\\\\\n  --target '{\\n    \\\"Arn\\\": \\\"<ECS_CLUSTER_ARN>\\\",\\n    \\\"RoleArn\\\": \\\"<SCHEDULER_ROLE_ARN>\\\",\\n    \\\"EcsParameters\\\": {\\n      \\\"TaskDefinitionArn\\\": \\\"<TASK_DEF_ARN>\\\",\\n      \\\"LaunchType\\\": \\\"FARGATE\\\",\\n      \\\"NetworkConfiguration\\\": { \\\"awsvpcConfiguration\\\": { \\\"Subnets\\\": [\\\"<SUBNET_ID>\\\"], \\\"AssignPublicIp\\\": \\\"DISABLED\\\" } }\\n    }\\n  }' \\\\\\n  --flexible-time-window '{\\\"Mode\\\": \\\"OFF\\\"}'\\n```\\n\\nThis runs `live_runner.js` as a short-lived task instead of a daemon — better for cost and observability.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Monitoring Hooks\\n\\nCloudWatch alarms are already wired in `infrastructure/main.tf` via the SNS module. For the trading pipeline specifically:\\n\\n| Alarm | Metric | Threshold | SNS Topic |\\n|-------|--------|-----------|-----------|\\n| Pipeline stopped | ECS RunningTaskCount = 0 | 5 min | `p0_critical` |\\n| High error rate | CW Logs filter: \\\"Pipeline FAILED\\\" | > 3 in 30 min | `p1_alert` |\\n| Dashboard unhealthy | ALB HealthyHostCount < 1 | 5 min | `p1_alert` |\\n| Memory pressure | ECS MemoryUtilization > 80% | 10 min | `infra_ops` |\\n\\nSubscribe your email to the SNS topics:\\n```bash\\naws sns subscribe \\\\\\n  --topic-arn <P0_CRITICAL_ARN> \\\\\\n  --protocol email \\\\\\n  --notification-endpoint your@email.com\\n```\\n\\nThe existing `monitor.js` (Liam's work) handles application-level alerts (stale data, PnL anomalies, failed trades) — those run inside the container and can POST to Slack or write to CloudWatch custom metrics.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Security Notes (coordinate with Heidi)\\n\\n1. **Secrets**: API keys via Secrets Manager only — never in task definition plaintext or env files\\n2. **Network**: ECS task runs in private subnets; ALB in public subnets. No direct internet access to container\\n3. **IAM least privilege**: ECS task role has read-only Secrets Manager + EFS read-write only\\n4. **PAPER_TRADING guard**: Default `true` in both Dockerfile and task definition — double protection against accidental live orders\\n5. **Auth**: `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` required for all `/api/*` endpoints (existing `requireAuth` middleware in `dashboard_api.js`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Quick-Start Checklist (Day 1)\\n\\n- [ ] AWS account + CLI configured\\n- [ ] ECR repo created\\n- [ ] Secrets created in Secrets Manager (KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY)\\n- [ ] `Dockerfile.trading` created at repo root\\n- [ ] `ecosystem.trading.config.js` created in `agents/bob/backend/`\\n- [ ] Docker image built and pushed to ECR\\n- [ ] Terraform applied (VPC, ECS cluster, ALB, EFS, SNS)\\n- [ ] ECS task definition created with secrets injection\\n- [ ] ECS service deployed and running (1 task)\\n- [ ] Health check passing (`/api/health` returns 200)\\n- [ ] CloudWatch log group showing scheduler cycles\\n- [ ] SNS email subscription confirmed for p0_critical alerts\\n- [ ] `PAPER_TRADING=true` verified in running task env\\n\\nTotal time: **~4-6 hours** for a single operator with AWS CLI access.\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":168,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":37244,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":168},\"output_tokens\":45,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"a35f73b9-caf3-4475-8e53-c1c9f7608f30\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:99:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01PnyXzB9vHCmPhoUC9V5Xah\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"File created successfully at: /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/output/cloud_deployment_plan.md\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"726bd0c3-89c9-4007-bfb2-76443f77b767\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-03T18:34:07.696Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"create\",\"filePath\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/output/cloud_deployment_plan.md\",\"content\":\"# Cloud Deployment Plan — Kalshi Trading Pipeline\\n**Author**: Quinn (Cloud Engineer)\\n**Task**: T267\\n**Date**: 2026-04-03\\n**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP notes where applicable\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nDeploy the Kalshi trading pipeline as a containerized workload on AWS. The system consists of three processes:\\n\\n| Process | Source | Port | Description |\\n|---------|--------|------|-------------|\\n| `kalshi-dashboard` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard_api.js` | 3200 | Trade signals API |\\n| `kalshi-scheduler` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/run_scheduler.sh` | — | Runs `live_runner.js` every 10 min |\\n| `kalshi-monitor` | `agents/bob/backend/dashboard/monitor.js` | — | Alerts if pipeline stalls |\\n\\nA one-person operator can deploy this in a single day following the steps below.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture\\n\\n```\\nInternet\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nRoute 53 (optional domain)\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nALB (HTTPS :443 → HTTP :3200)\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nECS Fargate Task (trading-pipeline)\\n  ├── kalshi-dashboard    :3200\\n  ├── kalshi-scheduler    (no port — cron loop)\\n  └── kalshi-monitor      (no port — polling loop)\\n    │\\n    ▼\\nAWS Secrets Manager\\n  └── KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY\\n```\\n\\nNo database required. Trade signals are written to JSON files; PnL state is file-based. EFS mounts the `agents/bob/output/` directory for persistence across task restarts.\\n\\n**Monthly cost estimate** (us-east-1, on-demand):\\n| Resource | Config | $/month |\\n|----------|--------|---------|\\n| ECS Fargate | 0.25 vCPU / 512 MB, 24×7 | ~$9 |\\n| ALB | 1 instance | ~$18 |\\n| EFS | < 1 GB | < $1 |\\n| Secrets Manager | 2 secrets | $0.80 |\\n| CloudWatch Logs | ~1 GB/mo | ~$0.50 |\\n| **Total** | | **~$29/month** |\\n\\nTo cut cost to ~$11/month: drop the ALB and expose the dashboard directly (no HTTPS) — acceptable for a single-operator internal tool.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Container Choice: AWS Fargate\\n\\n**Why Fargate over EC2:**\\n- No instance management, patching, or AMI rotation\\n- Scales to zero when stopped; billing is per-second\\n- Sufficient for a single trading pipeline (scheduler runs every 10 min, CPU burst only)\\n\\n**Why not Lambda:**\\n- The scheduler is a `while true; sleep 600` loop — Lambda's max execution time (15 min) doesn't fit\\n- live_runner.js needs persistent file output between runs\\n\\n**Why not GCP Cloud Run:**\\n- Existing Terraform modules are AWS-native (ECS, ALB, EFS, Secrets Manager)\\n- Switch to GCP Cloud Run only if Kalshi API latency to GCP us-central1 is significantly better\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Environment Variables\\n\\nInjected at runtime from **AWS Secrets Manager** — never hardcoded in container or task definition.\\n\\n| Variable | Required | Description |\\n|----------|----------|-------------|\\n| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Yes (live trading) | Kalshi REST API key — obtain from kalshi.com |\\n| `KALSHI_DEMO` | No | `\\\"false\\\"` = live mode; default = demo/paper mode |\\n| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Yes (production) | Bearer token for `/api/*` auth on port 3200 |\\n| `PAPER_TRADING` | No | Default `true` — set `\\\"false\\\"` only after founder approval |\\n| `NODE_ENV` | Yes | `\\\"production\\\"` |\\n| `PORT` | Yes | `3200` (dashboard API) |\\n\\n**Critical**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` is the default and must remain so until founder explicitly approves live order submission (per team consensus rule #1).\\n\\n### Secrets Manager setup (one-time)\\n```bash\\n# Create secrets\\naws secretsmanager create-secret \\\\\\n  --name \\\"tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\\\" \\\\\\n  --secret-string \\\"YOUR_KALSHI_API_KEY\\\"\\n\\naws secretsmanager create-secret \\\\\\n  --name \\\"tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\\\" \\\\\\n  --secret-string \\\"$(openssl rand -hex 32)\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Deployment Steps (Day 1)\\n\\n### Prerequisites\\n- AWS account with CLI configured (`aws configure`)\\n- Docker installed locally\\n- Terraform >= 1.6\\n- Node.js 20 (for local build/test)\\n\\n### Step 1: Build and push container image (~15 min)\\n\\n```bash\\n# From aicompany/ root\\ncd /path/to/aicompany\\n\\n# Create ECR repo (one-time)\\naws ecr create-repository --repository-name tokenfly-trading --region us-east-1\\n\\n# Authenticate Docker to ECR\\naws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 \\\\\\n  | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin \\\\\\n    <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com\\n\\n# Build trading pipeline image\\ndocker build -f Dockerfile.trading -t tokenfly-trading:latest .\\n\\n# Tag and push\\ndocker tag tokenfly-trading:latest \\\\\\n  <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest\\ndocker push <ACCOUNT_ID>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/tokenfly-trading:latest\\n```\\n\\n### Step 2: Create Dockerfile.trading\\n\\nThe existing `Dockerfile` serves the agent dashboard. The trading pipeline needs its own image:\\n\\n```dockerfile\\n# Dockerfile.trading\\nFROM node:20-alpine\\n\\nRUN apk add --no-cache bash\\n\\nWORKDIR /app\\n\\n# Install production deps\\nCOPY agents/bob/backend/package.json agents/bob/backend/package-lock.json ./\\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\\n\\n# Copy trading pipeline source\\nCOPY agents/bob/backend/ ./\\n\\n# Create output directory for trade signals\\nRUN mkdir -p /app/output\\n\\nEXPOSE 3200\\n\\nENV NODE_ENV=production \\\\\\n    PORT=3200 \\\\\\n    PAPER_TRADING=true\\n\\n# Start all three processes via PM2\\nRUN npm install -g pm2\\nCMD [\\\"pm2-runtime\\\", \\\"ecosystem.trading.config.js\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n### Step 3: Create PM2 config for trading processes\\n\\n```javascript\\n// ecosystem.trading.config.js\\nmodule.exports = {\\n  apps: [\\n    {\\n      name: \\\"kalshi-dashboard\\\",\\n      script: \\\"dashboard_api.js\\\",\\n      instances: 1,\\n      env: { NODE_ENV: \\\"production\\\", PORT: \\\"3200\\\" },\\n    },\\n    {\\n      name: \\\"kalshi-scheduler\\\",\\n      script: \\\"dashboard/run_scheduler.sh\\\",\\n      interpreter: \\\"bash\\\",\\n      instances: 1,\\n    },\\n    {\\n      name: \\\"kalshi-monitor\\\",\\n      script: \\\"dashboard/monitor.js\\\",\\n      instances: 1,\\n    },\\n  ],\\n};\\n```\\n\\n### Step 4: Provision infrastructure with Terraform (~10 min)\\n\\nUse the existing `infrastructure/` modules. Create a new `trading` environment or reuse `dev`:\\n\\n```bash\\ncd infrastructure/environments/dev   # or create environments/trading/\\n\\n# terraform.tfvars (trading-specific)\\ncat > terraform.tfvars <<EOF\\nenv                  = \\\"trading\\\"\\naws_region           = \\\"us-east-1\\\"\\nvpc_cidr             = \\\"10.1.0.0/16\\\"\\navailability_zones   = [\\\"us-east-1a\\\", \\\"us-east-1b\\\"]\\npublic_subnet_cidrs  = [\\\"10.1.0.0/24\\\", \\\"10.1.1.0/24\\\"]\\nprivate_subnet_cidrs = [\\\"10.1.2.0/24\\\", \\\"10.1.3.0/24\\\"]\\nnat_gateway_count    = 1\\ntask_cpu             = 256\\ntask_memory          = 512\\ndesired_count        = 1\\nmin_capacity         = 1\\nmax_capacity         = 1\\nimage_tag            = \\\"latest\\\"\\nEOF\\n\\nterraform init\\nterraform plan    # review — should create ~35 resources\\nterraform apply\\n```\\n\\n### Step 5: Deploy ECS task definition\\n\\nThe `infrastructure/modules/ecs` module creates the ECS service. Override the container definition to point to the trading image and inject secrets:\\n\\nAdd to `infrastructure/modules/ecs/main.tf` (or create `infrastructure/modules/trading_task/`):\\n\\n```hcl\\n# ECS Task Definition — Trading Pipeline\\nresource \\\"aws_ecs_task_definition\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  family                   = \\\"${var.name_prefix}-trading\\\"\\n  requires_compatibilities = [\\\"FARGATE\\\"]\\n  network_mode             = \\\"awsvpc\\\"\\n  cpu                      = 256\\n  memory                   = 512\\n  execution_role_arn       = aws_iam_role.ecs_execution.arn\\n  task_role_arn            = aws_iam_role.ecs_task.arn\\n\\n  container_definitions = jsonencode([\\n    {\\n      name  = \\\"trading-pipeline\\\"\\n      image = \\\"${var.ecr_repo_url}:${var.image_tag}\\\"\\n      portMappings = [{ containerPort = 3200, hostPort = 3200 }]\\n      \\n      secrets = [\\n        {\\n          name      = \\\"KALSHI_API_KEY\\\"\\n          valueFrom = \\\"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/kalshi-api-key\\\"\\n        },\\n        {\\n          name      = \\\"DASHBOARD_API_KEY\\\"\\n          valueFrom = \\\"arn:aws:secretsmanager:${var.aws_region}:${var.aws_account_id}:secret:tokenfly/trading/dashboard-api-key\\\"\\n        }\\n      ]\\n\\n      environment = [\\n        { name = \\\"NODE_ENV\\\",       value = \\\"production\\\" },\\n        { name = \\\"PORT\\\",           value = \\\"3200\\\" },\\n        { name = \\\"PAPER_TRADING\\\",  value = \\\"true\\\" },   # NEVER false without founder approval\\n        { name = \\\"KALSHI_DEMO\\\",    value = \\\"true\\\" }\\n      ]\\n\\n      mountPoints = [\\n        {\\n          sourceVolume  = \\\"trading-output\\\"\\n          containerPath = \\\"/app/output\\\"\\n          readOnly      = false\\n        }\\n      ]\\n\\n      logConfiguration = {\\n        logDriver = \\\"awslogs\\\"\\n        options = {\\n          awslogs-group         = \\\"/ecs/${var.name_prefix}-trading\\\"\\n          awslogs-region        = var.aws_region\\n          awslogs-stream-prefix = \\\"ecs\\\"\\n        }\\n      }\\n\\n      healthCheck = {\\n        command     = [\\\"CMD-SHELL\\\", \\\"node -e \\\\\\\"require('http').get('http://localhost:3200/api/health', r => process.exit(r.statusCode===200?0:1)).on('error',()=>process.exit(1))\\\\\\\"\\\"]\\n        interval    = 30\\n        timeout     = 5\\n        retries     = 3\\n        startPeriod = 15\\n      }\\n    }\\n  ])\\n\\n  volume {\\n    name = \\\"trading-output\\\"\\n    efs_volume_configuration {\\n      file_system_id     = var.efs_file_system_id\\n      transit_encryption = \\\"ENABLED\\\"\\n      authorization_config {\\n        access_point_id = var.efs_access_point_id\\n        iam             = \\\"ENABLED\\\"\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Step 6: Verify deployment (~5 min)\\n\\n```bash\\n# Check ECS service status\\naws ecs describe-services \\\\\\n  --cluster tokenfly-trading \\\\\\n  --services trading-pipeline \\\\\\n  --query 'services[0].{status:status,running:runningCount,desired:desiredCount}'\\n\\n# Tail CloudWatch logs\\naws logs tail /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading --follow\\n\\n# Test dashboard API via ALB\\ncurl -H \\\"x-api-key: $DASHBOARD_API_KEY\\\" \\\\\\n  https://<ALB_DNS>/api/health\\n\\n# Confirm scheduler is running (look for 10-min cycle logs)\\naws logs filter-log-events \\\\\\n  --log-group-name /ecs/tokenfly-trading-trading \\\\\\n  --filter-pattern \\\"Pipeline OK\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Scheduler: run_scheduler.sh on AWS\\n\\nThe scheduler (`dashboard/run_scheduler.sh`) runs as a sidecar process inside the same ECS task via PM2. It loops every 600 seconds calling `live_runner.js`.\\n\\n**Alternative: EventBridge Scheduler** (cleaner, more observable)\\n\\nIf the while-loop approach causes issues (e.g., task restarts lose state), migrate to EventBridge:\\n\\n```bash\\n# Create EventBridge rule — runs every 10 minutes\\naws scheduler create-schedule \\\\\\n  --name kalshi-pipeline-run \\\\\\n  --schedule-expression \\\"rate(10 minutes)\\\" \\\\\\n  --target '{\\n    \\\"Arn\\\": \\\"<ECS_CLUSTER_ARN>\\\",\\n    \\\"RoleArn\\\": \\\"<SCHEDULER_ROLE_ARN>\\\",\\n    \\\"EcsParameters\\\": {\\n      \\\"TaskDefinitionArn\\\": \\\"<TASK_DEF_ARN>\\\",\\n      \\\"LaunchType\\\": \\\"FARGATE\\\",\\n      \\\"NetworkConfiguration\\\": { \\\"awsvpcConfiguration\\\": { \\\"Subnets\\\": [\\\"<SUBNET_ID>\\\"], \\\"AssignPublicIp\\\": \\\"DISABLED\\\" } }\\n    }\\n  }' \\\\\\n  --flexible-time-window '{\\\"Mode\\\": \\\"OFF\\\"}'\\n```\\n\\nThis runs `live_runner.js` as a short-lived task instead of a daemon — better for cost and observability.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Monitoring Hooks\\n\\nCloudWatch alarms are already wired in `infrastructure/main.tf` via the SNS module. For the trading pipeline specifically:\\n\\n| Alarm | Metric | Threshold | SNS Topic |\\n|-------|--------|-----------|-----------|\\n| Pipeline stopped | ECS RunningTaskCount = 0 | 5 min | `p0_critical` |\\n| High error rate | CW Logs filter: \\\"Pipeline FAILED\\\" | > 3 in 30 min | `p1_alert` |\\n| Dashboard unhealthy | ALB HealthyHostCount < 1 | 5 min | `p1_alert` |\\n| Memory pressure | ECS MemoryUtilization > 80% | 10 min | `infra_ops` |\\n\\nSubscribe your email to the SNS topics:\\n```bash\\naws sns subscribe \\\\\\n  --topic-arn <P0_CRITICAL_ARN> \\\\\\n  --protocol email \\\\\\n  --notification-endpoint your@email.com\\n```\\n\\nThe existing `monitor.js` (Liam's work) handles application-level alerts (stale data, PnL anomalies, failed trades) — those run inside the container and can POST to Slack or write to CloudWatch custom metrics.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Security Notes (coordinate with Heidi)\\n\\n1. **Secrets**: API keys via Secrets Manager only — never in task definition plaintext or env files\\n2. **Network**: ECS task runs in private subnets; ALB in public subnets. No direct internet access to container\\n3. **IAM least privilege**: ECS task role has read-only Secrets Manager + EFS read-write only\\n4. **PAPER_TRADING guard**: Default `true` in both Dockerfile and task definition — double protection against accidental live orders\\n5. **Auth**: `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` required for all `/api/*` endpoints (existing `requireAuth` middleware in `dashboard_api.js`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Quick-Start Checklist (Day 1)\\n\\n- [ ] AWS account + CLI configured\\n- [ ] ECR repo created\\n- [ ] Secrets created in Secrets Manager (KALSHI_API_KEY, DASHBOARD_API_KEY)\\n- [ ] `Dockerfile.trading` created at repo root\\n- [ ] `ecosystem.trading.config.js` created in `agents/bob/backend/`\\n- [ ] Docker image built and pushed to ECR\\n- [ ] Terraform applied (VPC, ECS cluster, ALB, EFS, SNS)\\n- [ ] ECS task definition created with secrets injection\\n- [ ] ECS service deployed and running (1 task)\\n- [ ] Health check passing (`/api/health` returns 200)\\n- [ ] CloudWatch log group showing scheduler cycles\\n- [ ] SNS email subscription confirmed for p0_critical alerts\\n- [ ] `PAPER_TRADING=true` verified in running task env\\n\\nTotal time: **~4-6 hours** for a single operator with AWS CLI access.\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[],\"originalFile\":null}}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:100:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014rPPbLE9VHxbB4brsXs174\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01JmPTTkicrDnuoDVJxtVag1\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"# Move inbox messages to processed\\ncd /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/chat_inbox\\nmv 2026_04_03_11_31_04_from_ceo.md processed/\\nmv from_alice_t267_2026_04_03_11_31_33.md processed/\\nmv 2026_04_03_11_17_13_from_alice_t267.md processed/\\nmv 2026_04_03_02_01_17_from_alice.md processed/\\necho \\\"Inbox cleared\\\"\",\"description\":\"Archive inbox messages\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4284,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":37412,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4284},\"output_tokens\":35,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"c108ebbd-e8e9-4eb4-af0f-9f79b3f28574\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:101:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01JmPTTkicrDnuoDVJxtVag1\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"Inbox cleared\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"55d0b29b-38bf-4f60-ae12-21e9a5b8f42a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-03T18:34:13.547Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"Inbox cleared\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false}}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:102:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_014rPPbLE9VHxbB4brsXs174\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_012n8Sm2M83Ct6pTyhqJMJw2\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"# Mark task 267 done\\ncurl -s -X PATCH http://localhost:3199/api/tasks/267 \\\\\\n  -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" \\\\\\n  -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\"}'\",\"description\":\"Mark Task 267 done\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4284,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":37412,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4284},\"output_tokens\":35,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"2e0245be-0cc8-4998-97a0-456c8a713cfa\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:103:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_012n8Sm2M83Ct6pTyhqJMJw2\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"{\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"task_type\\\":\\\"task\\\",\\\"id\\\":267,\\\"title\\\":\\\"Cloud: design deployment plan for trading pipeline on AWS (or GCP)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Design a cloud deployment architecture for the Kalshi trading system. Cover: where live_runner.js runs (EC2/Cloud Run/Lambda), secrets management for KALSHI_API_KEY, scheduling (cron every 5min), cost estimate. Output: cloud_deployment_plan.md\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"group\\\":\\\"all\\\",\\\"assignee\\\":\\\"quinn\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\",\\\"created\\\":\\\"2026-04-03\\\",\\\"updated\\\":\\\"2026-04-03\\\",\\\"notes\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"notesList\\\":[]}\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"9eacdfff-e892-4aa0-859c-f36b693b2402\",\"uuid\":\"535f5e36-82e6-4ae0-a8d7-c703c7b76609\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-03T18:34:14.390Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\\"ok\\\":true,\\\"task_type\\\":\\\"task\\\",\\\"id\\\":267,\\\"title\\\":\\\"Cloud: design deployment plan for trading pipeline on AWS (or GCP)\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Design a cloud deployment architecture for the Kalshi trading system. Cover: where live_runner.js runs (EC2/Cloud Run/Lambda), secrets management for KALSHI_API_KEY, scheduling (cron every 5min), cost estimate. Output: cloud_deployment_plan.md\\\",\\\"priority\\\":\\\"medium\\\",\\\"group\\\":\\\"all\\\",\\\"assignee\\\":\\\"quinn\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\",\\\"created\\\":\\\"2026-04-03\\\",\\\"updated\\\":\\\"2026-04-03\\\",\\\"notes\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"notesList\\\":[]}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false}}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:104:{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_015H4zLEMCJdCsgnfyYdq3ng\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01AdwkQyuAJRcSZ2wQC2qRi1\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/agents/quinn/output/cloud_deployment_plan.md\",\"content\":\"# Cloud Deployment Plan — Kalshi Trading Pipeline\\n**Author**: Quinn (Cloud Engineer)\\n**Task**: T267\\n**Date**: 2026-04-03\\n**Target**: AWS (primary) with GCP alternative noted\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Architecture Overview\\n\\n```\\n                          ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n                          │              AWS VPC (us-east-1)         │\\n                          │                                           │\\n  Internet ───── ALB ──── │ ── EC2 t3.small ──────────────────────── │\\n  (HTTPS:443)   (port 80) │   ┌───────────────────────────────────┐  │\\n                          │   │  Docker Compose                   │  │\\n                          │   │  ┌─────────────┐ ┌─────────────┐  │  │\\n                          │   │  │  dashboard  │ │  trading-   │  │  │\\n                          │   │  │  (port 3199)│ │  api(:8080) │  │  │\\n                          │   │  └─────────────┘ └──────┬──────┘  │  │\\n                          │   │  ┌─────────────────────────────┐  │  │\\n                          │   │  │  scheduler (cron every 10m) │  │  │\\n                          │   │  └─────────────────────────────┘  │  │\\n                          │   └───────────────────────────────────┘  │\\n                          │                    │                       │\\n                          │   RDS PostgreSQL ──┘                      │\\n                          │   (db.t3.micro)                           │\\n                          └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n                                      │\\n                               Secrets Manager\\n                               (KALSHI_API_KEY, DB creds)\\n                                      │\\n                               CloudWatch Logs\\n                               (pipeline + dashboard logs)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Why This Architecture\\n\\n**Single EC2 + Docker Compose** rather than ECS/EKS:\\n- One person can deploy in a day\\n- No cluster management overhead\\n- The existing `Dockerfile` and `docker-compose.yml` work as-is with minor additions\\n- Easy SSH access for debugging during early production phase\\n- Total cost: ~$35/month (vs $100+/month for ECS Fargate + ALB)\\n\\nUpgrade path: Once trading is proven in production, migrate trading-api to ECS Fargate without changing application code.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step-by-Step Deployment\\n\\n### 1. Prerequisites (30 min)\\n\\n```bash\\n# Install AWS CLI\\nbrew install awscli\\naws configure  # set region us-east-1\\n\\n# Install Terraform\\nbrew install terraform\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Terraform — VPC + EC2 + RDS + Secrets (IaC)\\n\\nSave as `infrastructure/trading/main.tf`:\\n\\n```hcl\\nterraform {\\n  required_providers {\\n    aws = { source = \\\"hashicorp/aws\\\", version = \\\"~> 5.0\\\" }\\n  }\\n  backend \\\"s3\\\" {\\n    bucket = \\\"tokenfly-tf-state\\\"\\n    key    = \\\"trading/terraform.tfstate\\\"\\n    region = \\\"us-east-1\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nprovider \\\"aws\\\" { region = \\\"us-east-1\\\" }\\n\\n# ── VPC ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nresource \\\"aws_vpc\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  cidr_block           = \\\"10.0.0.0/16\\\"\\n  enable_dns_hostnames = true\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-trading\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_internet_gateway\\\" \\\"igw\\\" {\\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\\n  tags   = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-igw\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_subnet\\\" \\\"public_a\\\" {\\n  vpc_id                  = aws_vpc.trading.id\\n  cidr_block              = \\\"10.0.1.0/24\\\"\\n  availability_zone       = \\\"us-east-1a\\\"\\n  map_public_ip_on_launch = true\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-public-a\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_subnet\\\" \\\"private_a\\\" {\\n  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id\\n  cidr_block        = \\\"10.0.10.0/24\\\"\\n  availability_zone = \\\"us-east-1a\\\"\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-private-a\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_subnet\\\" \\\"private_b\\\" {\\n  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.trading.id\\n  cidr_block        = \\\"10.0.11.0/24\\\"\\n  availability_zone = \\\"us-east-1b\\\"\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-private-b\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_route_table\\\" \\\"public\\\" {\\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\\n  route {\\n    cidr_block = \\\"0.0.0.0/0\\\"\\n    gateway_id = aws_internet_gateway.igw.id\\n  }\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-public-rt\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_route_table_association\\\" \\\"public_a\\\" {\\n  subnet_id      = aws_subnet.public_a.id\\n  route_table_id = aws_route_table.public.id\\n}\\n\\n# ── Security Groups ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nresource \\\"aws_security_group\\\" \\\"ec2\\\" {\\n  name   = \\\"tokenfly-ec2\\\"\\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\\n\\n  # HTTPS from anywhere (ALB forwards here, or direct HTTPS if no ALB)\\n  ingress {\\n    from_port   = 3199\\n    to_port     = 3199\\n    protocol    = \\\"tcp\\\"\\n    cidr_blocks = [\\\"0.0.0.0/0\\\"]  # Lock to your IP in production\\n  }\\n  ingress {\\n    from_port   = 22\\n    to_port     = 22\\n    protocol    = \\\"tcp\\\"\\n    cidr_blocks = [\\\"0.0.0.0/0\\\"]  # Lock to your IP: [\\\"YOUR_IP/32\\\"]\\n  }\\n  egress {\\n    from_port   = 0\\n    to_port     = 0\\n    protocol    = \\\"-1\\\"\\n    cidr_blocks = [\\\"0.0.0.0/0\\\"]\\n  }\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-ec2-sg\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_security_group\\\" \\\"rds\\\" {\\n  name   = \\\"tokenfly-rds\\\"\\n  vpc_id = aws_vpc.trading.id\\n\\n  ingress {\\n    from_port       = 5432\\n    to_port         = 5432\\n    protocol        = \\\"tcp\\\"\\n    security_groups = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]  # EC2 only\\n  }\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-rds-sg\\\" }\\n}\\n\\n# ── RDS PostgreSQL ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nresource \\\"aws_db_subnet_group\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  name       = \\\"tokenfly-trading\\\"\\n  subnet_ids = [aws_subnet.private_a.id, aws_subnet.private_b.id]\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_db_instance\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  identifier        = \\\"tokenfly-trading\\\"\\n  engine            = \\\"postgres\\\"\\n  engine_version    = \\\"16.3\\\"\\n  instance_class    = \\\"db.t3.micro\\\"  # $15/month\\n  allocated_storage = 20\\n  storage_type      = \\\"gp2\\\"\\n\\n  db_name  = \\\"kalshi_trading\\\"\\n  username = \\\"trading_user\\\"\\n  password = random_password.db.result\\n\\n  db_subnet_group_name   = aws_db_subnet_group.trading.name\\n  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.rds.id]\\n\\n  backup_retention_period = 7\\n  deletion_protection     = true\\n  skip_final_snapshot     = false\\n  final_snapshot_identifier = \\\"tokenfly-trading-final\\\"\\n\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-trading-db\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"random_password\\\" \\\"db\\\" {\\n  length  = 32\\n  special = false\\n}\\n\\n# ── EC2 Instance ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\ndata \\\"aws_ami\\\" \\\"amazon_linux_2023\\\" {\\n  most_recent = true\\n  owners      = [\\\"amazon\\\"]\\n  filter {\\n    name   = \\\"name\\\"\\n    values = [\\\"al2023-ami-*-x86_64\\\"]\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_iam_role\\\" \\\"ec2\\\" {\\n  name = \\\"tokenfly-ec2-role\\\"\\n  assume_role_policy = jsonencode({\\n    Version = \\\"2012-10-17\\\"\\n    Statement = [{\\n      Action    = \\\"sts:AssumeRole\\\"\\n      Effect    = \\\"Allow\\\"\\n      Principal = { Service = \\\"ec2.amazonaws.com\\\" }\\n    }]\\n  })\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_iam_role_policy_attachment\\\" \\\"ssm\\\" {\\n  role       = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\\n  policy_arn = \\\"arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore\\\"\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_iam_role_policy\\\" \\\"secrets\\\" {\\n  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\\n  policy = jsonencode({\\n    Version = \\\"2012-10-17\\\"\\n    Statement = [{\\n      Effect   = \\\"Allow\\\"\\n      Action   = [\\\"secretsmanager:GetSecretValue\\\"]\\n      Resource = [aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn]\\n    }, {\\n      Effect   = \\\"Allow\\\"\\n      Action   = [\\\"logs:CreateLogGroup\\\", \\\"logs:CreateLogStream\\\", \\\"logs:PutLogEvents\\\"]\\n      Resource = \\\"arn:aws:logs:*:*:*\\\"\\n    }]\\n  })\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_iam_instance_profile\\\" \\\"ec2\\\" {\\n  name = \\\"tokenfly-ec2-profile\\\"\\n  role = aws_iam_role.ec2.name\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_instance\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  ami                  = data.aws_ami.amazon_linux_2023.id\\n  instance_type        = \\\"t3.small\\\"  # 2 vCPU, 2 GB RAM — $15/month\\n  subnet_id            = aws_subnet.public_a.id\\n  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.ec2.id]\\n  iam_instance_profile = aws_iam_instance_profile.ec2.name\\n  key_name             = var.key_pair_name\\n\\n  root_block_device {\\n    volume_size = 20\\n    volume_type = \\\"gp3\\\"\\n  }\\n\\n  user_data = templatefile(\\\"${path.module}/user_data.sh\\\", {\\n    secret_arn = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.arn\\n    db_host    = aws_db_instance.trading.address\\n    db_name    = aws_db_instance.trading.db_name\\n    db_user    = aws_db_instance.trading.username\\n    aws_region = \\\"us-east-1\\\"\\n  })\\n\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-trading\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_eip\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  instance = aws_instance.trading.id\\n  domain   = \\\"vpc\\\"\\n  tags     = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-trading-eip\\\" }\\n}\\n\\n# ── Secrets Manager ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nresource \\\"aws_secretsmanager_secret\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  name                    = \\\"tokenfly/trading\\\"\\n  recovery_window_in_days = 7\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-trading-secrets\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_secretsmanager_secret_version\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  secret_id = aws_secretsmanager_secret.trading.id\\n  secret_string = jsonencode({\\n    KALSHI_API_KEY    = var.kalshi_api_key\\n    API_KEY           = var.dashboard_api_key\\n    DASHBOARD_API_KEY = var.dashboard_api_key\\n    JWT_SECRET        = random_password.jwt.result\\n    DB_PASSWORD       = random_password.db.result\\n    TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK = var.trading_alert_webhook\\n  })\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"random_password\\\" \\\"jwt\\\" {\\n  length  = 64\\n  special = false\\n}\\n\\n# ── CloudWatch Log Groups ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nresource \\\"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\\\" \\\"pipeline\\\" {\\n  name              = \\\"/tokenfly/trading/pipeline\\\"\\n  retention_in_days = 30\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-pipeline-logs\\\" }\\n}\\n\\nresource \\\"aws_cloudwatch_log_group\\\" \\\"dashboard\\\" {\\n  name              = \\\"/tokenfly/trading/dashboard\\\"\\n  retention_in_days = 14\\n  tags = { Name = \\\"tokenfly-dashboard-logs\\\" }\\n}\\n\\n# ── Cost Alert ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nresource \\\"aws_budgets_budget\\\" \\\"trading\\\" {\\n  name         = \\\"tokenfly-trading-monthly\\\"\\n  budget_type  = \\\"COST\\\"\\n  limit_amount = \\\"60\\\"\\n  limit_unit   = \\\"USD\\\"\\n  time_unit    = \\\"MONTHLY\\\"\\n\\n  notification {\\n    comparison_operator = \\\"GREATER_THAN\\\"\\n    threshold           = 80\\n    threshold_type      = \\\"PERCENTAGE\\\"\\n    notification_type   = \\\"ACTUAL\\\"\\n    subscriber_email_addresses = [var.alert_email]\\n  }\\n}\\n\\n# ── Variables ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\nvariable \\\"kalshi_api_key\\\"       { sensitive = true }\\nvariable \\\"dashboard_api_key\\\"    { sensitive = true }\\nvariable \\\"trading_alert_webhook\\\" { default = \\\"\\\" }\\nvariable \\\"key_pair_name\\\"        { default = \\\"tokenfly-trading\\\" }\\nvariable \\\"alert_email\\\"          {}\\n\\n# ── Outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\\noutput \\\"instance_ip\\\"  { value = aws_eip.trading.public_ip }\\noutput \\\"db_endpoint\\\"  { value = aws_db_instance.trading.address, sensitive = true }\\noutput \\\"ssh_command\\\"  { value = \\\"ssh -i ~/.ssh/${var.key_pair_name}.pem ec2-user@${aws_eip.trading.public_ip}\\\" }\\n```\\n\\n### 3. EC2 Bootstrap Script (`infrastructure/trading/user_data.sh`)\\n\\n```bash\\n#!/bin/bash\\nset -e\\n\\n# Install Docker + Docker Compose\\ndnf install -y docker aws-cli\\nsystemctl enable docker\\nsystemctl start docker\\nmkdir -p /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins\\ncurl -sL \\\"https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/latest/download/docker-compose-linux-x86_64\\\" \\\\\\n  -o /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose\\nchmod +x /usr/local/lib/docker/cli-plugins/docker-compose\\nusermod -aG docker ec2-user\\n\\n# Install CloudWatch agent\\ndnf install -y amazon-cloudwatch-agent\\n\\n# Fetch secrets from Secrets Manager\\nSECRET=$(aws secretsmanager get-secret-value \\\\\\n  --secret-id \\\"${secret_arn}\\\" \\\\\\n  --region \\\"${aws_region}\\\" \\\\\\n  --query SecretString --output text)\\n\\n# Write env file (not world-readable)\\nmkdir -p /opt/tokenfly\\ncat > /opt/tokenfly/.env << EOF\\nNODE_ENV=production\\nPAPER_TRADING=true\\n\\n# Kalshi API\\nKALSHI_API_KEY=$(echo \\\"$SECRET\\\" | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['KALSHI_API_KEY'])\\\")\\n\\n# Dashboard auth\\nAPI_KEY=$(echo \\\"$SECRET\\\" | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['API_KEY'])\\\")\\nDASHBOARD_API_KEY=$(echo \\\"$SECRET\\\" | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['DASHBOARD_API_KEY'])\\\")\\n\\n# JWT\\nJWT_SECRET=$(echo \\\"$SECRET\\\" | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['JWT_SECRET'])\\\")\\n\\n# Database (RDS)\\nDB_HOST=${db_host}\\nDB_PORT=5432\\nDB_NAME=${db_name}\\nDB_USER=${db_user}\\nDB_PASSWORD=$(echo \\\"$SECRET\\\" | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin)['DB_PASSWORD'])\\\")\\nPGSSLMODE=require\\n\\n# Trading limits (conservative defaults)\\nMAX_POSITION_SIZE=50\\nMAX_DAILY_LOSS=200\\nMAX_DRAWDOWN=10\\nMAX_TOTAL_EXPOSURE=500\\nMAX_CONCENTRATION=20\\n\\n# Alerts\\nTRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK=$(echo \\\"$SECRET\\\" | python3 -c \\\"import sys,json; print(json.load(sys.stdin).get('TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK',''))\\\")\\nEOF\\nchmod 600 /opt/tokenfly/.env\\n\\n# Clone repo\\ncd /opt/tokenfly\\ngit clone https://github.com/tokenflyai/aicompany.git .  # Replace with actual repo\\n\\n# Initialize DB schema\\nexport $(cat .env | xargs)\\ncd agents/bob/backend\\nnode -e \\\"\\nconst { Pool } = require('pg');\\nconst fs = require('fs');\\nconst pool = new Pool();\\nconst schema = fs.readFileSync('db/schema.sql','utf8') +\\n               fs.readFileSync('db/schema_strategies.sql','utf8') +\\n               fs.readFileSync('db/schema_risk.sql','utf8');\\npool.query(schema).then(() => { console.log('DB init OK'); process.exit(0); }).catch(e => { console.error(e); process.exit(1); });\\n\\\"\\ncd /opt/tokenfly\\n\\n# Write docker-compose.prod.yml\\ncat > /opt/tokenfly/docker-compose.prod.yml << 'COMPOSE'\\nversion: \\\"3.9\\\"\\nservices:\\n  dashboard:\\n    build:\\n      context: .\\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile\\n    container_name: tokenfly-dashboard\\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\\n    ports:\\n      - \\\"3199:3199\\\"\\n    volumes:\\n      - ./agents:/app/agents\\n      - ./public:/app/public\\n      - /tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs:/tmp/aicompany_runtime_logs\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    logging:\\n      driver: awslogs\\n      options:\\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/dashboard\\n        awslogs-region: ${aws_region}\\n        awslogs-stream: dashboard\\n\\n  trading-api:\\n    build:\\n      context: ./agents/bob/backend\\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile.api\\n    container_name: tokenfly-trading-api\\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\\n    ports:\\n      - \\\"8080:8080\\\"\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    logging:\\n      driver: awslogs\\n      options:\\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline\\n        awslogs-region: ${aws_region}\\n        awslogs-stream: trading-api\\n\\n  scheduler:\\n    build:\\n      context: ./agents/bob/backend\\n      dockerfile: Dockerfile.scheduler\\n    container_name: tokenfly-scheduler\\n    env_file: /opt/tokenfly/.env\\n    restart: unless-stopped\\n    logging:\\n      driver: awslogs\\n      options:\\n        awslogs-group: /tokenfly/trading/pipeline\\n        awslogs-region: ${aws_region}\\n        awslogs-stream: scheduler\\nCOMPOSE\\n\\n# Start services\\ndocker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --build\\n\\necho \\\"Tokenfly trading stack started\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Dockerfiles for Trading Backend\\n\\n`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.api`:\\n```dockerfile\\nFROM node:20-alpine\\nWORKDIR /app\\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json ./\\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\\nCOPY . .\\nEXPOSE 8080\\nENV PORT=8080\\nCMD [\\\"node\\\", \\\"api/server.js\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n`agents/bob/backend/Dockerfile.scheduler`:\\n```dockerfile\\nFROM node:20-alpine\\nWORKDIR /app\\nCOPY package.json package-lock.json ./\\nRUN npm ci --omit=dev\\nCOPY . .\\n# Run live_runner.js every 10 minutes (replaces run_scheduler.sh)\\nCMD [\\\"sh\\\", \\\"-c\\\", \\\"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\\\"]\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Terraform Variables (`infrastructure/trading/terraform.tfvars`)\\n\\n```hcl\\n# !! Never commit this file — add to .gitignore !!\\nkalshi_api_key       = \\\"your-kalshi-api-key-here\\\"\\ndashboard_api_key    = \\\"your-dashboard-api-key-here\\\"\\ntrading_alert_webhook = \\\"https://hooks.slack.com/services/...\\\"\\nkey_pair_name        = \\\"tokenfly-trading\\\"\\nalert_email          = \\\"alerts@tokenfly.ai\\\"\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Deploy Commands (One-Time Setup)\\n\\n```bash\\n# 1. Create SSH key pair\\naws ec2 create-key-pair \\\\\\n  --key-name tokenfly-trading \\\\\\n  --query 'KeyMaterial' \\\\\\n  --output text > ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem\\nchmod 400 ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem\\n\\n# 2. Create S3 bucket for Terraform state\\naws s3api create-bucket \\\\\\n  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\\\\n  --region us-east-1\\naws s3api put-bucket-versioning \\\\\\n  --bucket tokenfly-tf-state \\\\\\n  --versioning-configuration Status=Enabled\\n\\n# 3. Deploy with Terraform\\ncd infrastructure/trading\\nterraform init\\nterraform plan -var-file=terraform.tfvars\\nterraform apply -var-file=terraform.tfvars\\n\\n# 4. Verify\\nINSTANCE_IP=$(terraform output -raw instance_ip)\\nssh -i ~/.ssh/tokenfly-trading.pem ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\\\\\n  \\\"docker ps && curl -s http://localhost:3199/api/health\\\"\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Environment Variables Reference\\n\\n| Variable | Where Set | Description |\\n|----------|-----------|-------------|\\n| `KALSHI_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Kalshi trading API credentials |\\n| `API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Dashboard API auth token |\\n| `DASHBOARD_API_KEY` | Secrets Manager | Alias for API_KEY (dashboard calls) |\\n| `JWT_SECRET` | Secrets Manager | JWT signing key (64-char random) |\\n| `DB_HOST` | user_data (auto) | RDS endpoint from Terraform |\\n| `DB_PORT` | user_data | 5432 |\\n| `DB_NAME` | user_data | `kalshi_trading` |\\n| `DB_USER` | user_data | `trading_user` |\\n| `DB_PASSWORD` | Secrets Manager | RDS password (auto-generated by Terraform) |\\n| `PGSSLMODE` | user_data | `require` (RDS enforces SSL) |\\n| `PAPER_TRADING` | user_data | `true` (override to `false` for live) |\\n| `KALSHI_DEMO` | optional | `1` to hit demo API instead of live |\\n| `MAX_POSITION_SIZE` | user_data | Max contracts per position (default: 50) |\\n| `MAX_DAILY_LOSS` | user_data | Daily loss ceiling in USD (default: 200) |\\n| `MAX_DRAWDOWN` | user_data | Max drawdown % (default: 10) |\\n| `TRADING_ALERT_WEBHOOK` | Secrets Manager | Slack/webhook URL for trade alerts |\\n| `NODE_ENV` | user_data | `production` |\\n\\n**Critical**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` is the default. Changing to `false` requires explicit Founder approval (see consensus.md entry #1).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Scheduler Design\\n\\nThe trading pipeline runs `live_runner.js` every 10 minutes. Two options:\\n\\n### Option A: Container with while loop (recommended — simplest)\\n```dockerfile\\nCMD [\\\"sh\\\", \\\"-c\\\", \\\"while true; do node strategies/live_runner.js; sleep 600; done\\\"]\\n```\\n- Already done in `Dockerfile.scheduler` above\\n- Docker `restart: unless-stopped` handles crashes\\n- Logs go to CloudWatch via awslogs driver\\n\\n### Option B: AWS EventBridge Scheduler (serverless, zero idle cost)\\n```hcl\\nresource \\\"aws_scheduler_schedule\\\" \\\"pipeline\\\" {\\n  name = \\\"tokenfly-trading-pipeline\\\"\\n  flexible_time_window { mode = \\\"OFF\\\" }\\n  schedule_expression = \\\"rate(10 minutes)\\\"\\n  target {\\n    arn      = aws_ecs_task_definition.runner.arn  # requires ECS\\n    role_arn = aws_iam_role.scheduler.arn\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nUse Option B when/if migrating to ECS for zero idle compute cost on the scheduler.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Monitoring\\n\\n### CloudWatch Dashboard (manual setup, one-time)\\n```bash\\naws cloudwatch put-dashboard --dashboard-name TokenflyTrading \\\\\\n  --dashboard-body '{\\n    \\\"widgets\\\": [\\n      {\\\"type\\\":\\\"log\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Pipeline Runs\\\",\\\"logGroupName\\\":\\\"/tokenfly/trading/pipeline\\\",\\\"queryString\\\":\\\"fields @timestamp, @message | filter @message like /Pipeline/ | sort @timestamp desc | limit 50\\\"}},\\n      {\\\"type\\\":\\\"metric\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"EC2 CPU\\\",\\\"metrics\\\":[[\\\"AWS/EC2\\\",\\\"CPUUtilization\\\",\\\"InstanceId\\\",\\\"INSTANCE_ID\\\"]]}}\\n    ]\\n  }'\\n```\\n\\n### Alerts to add (via Terraform or console)\\n1. **Pipeline failure alert**: CloudWatch metric filter on `Pipeline FAILED` → SNS → email/Slack\\n2. **EC2 CPU > 80%**: CloudWatch alarm → SNS\\n3. **RDS storage < 2GB**: CloudWatch alarm → SNS\\n4. **Budget 80% threshold**: Already in Terraform (alerts to `alert_email`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Monthly Cost Estimate\\n\\n| Resource | Spec | Cost/month |\\n|----------|------|------------|\\n| EC2 t3.small | 2 vCPU, 2GB RAM | ~$15 |\\n| RDS db.t3.micro | PostgreSQL 16 | ~$15 |\\n| EBS gp3 20GB (EC2) | Root volume | ~$2 |\\n| RDS storage 20GB | gp2 | ~$2 |\\n| Elastic IP | Static IP | ~$4 |\\n| CloudWatch Logs | ~5 GB/month | ~$3 |\\n| Secrets Manager | 1 secret | ~$0.40 |\\n| Data transfer | ~10 GB/month | ~$1 |\\n| **Total** | | **~$42/month** |\\n\\nCost alert set at $48 (80% of $60 budget) in Terraform.\\n\\n**GCP equivalent** (if preferred): e2-small ($13) + Cloud SQL pg-micro ($10) + Cloud Logging ≈ $35/month. Same architecture, swap `aws_` providers for `google_`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Security Notes\\n\\n1. **Network**: RDS is in private subnets — unreachable from internet. EC2 is the only DB client.\\n2. **Secrets**: API keys never in env file on disk in plaintext for long — fetched from Secrets Manager at boot, written to `/opt/tokenfly/.env` with `chmod 600`. Rotate keys by updating the Secrets Manager secret and running `terraform apply`.\\n3. **SSH access**: Lock the EC2 security group `ingress port 22` to your IP once deployed (update `cidr_blocks = [\\\"YOUR_IP/32\\\"]`).\\n4. **Paper trading gate**: `PAPER_TRADING=true` by default. The live_runner.js enforces this: `const PAPER_TRADING = process.env.PAPER_TRADING !== 'false'`. Flip only with Founder approval.\\n5. **IAM least-privilege**: EC2 role has only Secrets Manager read + CloudWatch write. No S3, no EC2 describe, no admin.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Rollback Procedure\\n\\n```bash\\n# Stop containers without destroying infrastructure\\nssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\\"docker compose -f /opt/tokenfly/docker-compose.prod.yml down\\\"\\n\\n# Roll back to previous image tag (if using versioned images)\\nssh ec2-user@$INSTANCE_IP \\\"docker compose -f /opt/tokenfly/docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --scale trading-api=0\\\"\\n\\n# Destroy everything (WARNING: deletes RDS — snapshot taken first)\\ncd infrastructure/trading && terraform destroy -var-file=terraform.tfvars\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Day-One Checklist\\n\\n- [ ] `aws configure` with IAM user that has EC2, RDS, Secrets Manager, IAM, S3, Budgets permissions\\n- [ ] Create SSH key pair: `aws ec2 create-key-pair --key-name tokenfly-trading`\\n- [ ] Fill in `terraform.tfvars` with real values (never commit)\\n- [ ] `terraform init && terraform apply`\\n- [ ] SSH in, verify `docker ps` shows 3 containers running\\n- [ ] Hit `curl http://$INSTANCE_IP:3199/api/health` — expect `{\\\"ok\\\":true}`\\n- [ ] Tail pipeline log: `docker logs -f tokenfly-scheduler`\\n- [ ] Confirm `PAPER_TRADING=true` before any order execution\\n- [ ] Lock SSH security group to your IP\\n- [ ] Set up CloudWatch alerts for pipeline failures\\n\\n---\\n\\n*Quinn — Cloud Engineer | Agent Planet*\\n*All infrastructure is defined in `infrastructure/trading/` — no manual console changes.*\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"stop_details\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":372,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":34043,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":372},\"output_tokens\":45,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"fce96880-26d9-456d-a3be-a680ae78ce46\",\"uuid\":\"6637b177-a069-42c9-bd8b-a6487fc143ce\"}\n./logs/2026_04_03_raw.log:105:{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"<tool_use_error>File has not b